reviews.review_text: Garys is a great spot - a nice combination of cozy neighborhood spot and special event destination dining.  The food is really well executed and luxurious without being fussy.  Owners Bailey and Mat (of whom weve been fans since their days with Collective Hospitality) have nailed it with comfortable, friendly service and excellent food.  We went for a special event and will keep coming back, just because its worth the trip. Vegetarian options: Great options for most dietary restrictions and preferences.  The staff is super helpful and friendly with suggestions.

Very chill room, with excellent, attentive service and delicious, inventive twists on French/Euro classics. Unbelievable value at $64/pp for the tasting menu. What was unexpected was that the dishes we werent considering a la carte turned out to be total hits. The raddiccio, cheddar, apple and ham salad was incredible - light, with a sweet and savory balance. The lingcod had the most ethereal vadouvan spiced sauce and flavourful fingerling potatoes. And the sauce gribiche for the cured steelhead was a standout. The final savoury course - the pork cheeks with spaetzle, plentiful chanterelles and sourdough breadcrumb - was perfection. Loved everything about the place, and unbeatable value with todays prices. Highly recommend.

Chic but unassuming decor, attentive but relaxed service and the food was sublime. The ingredients were fresh and seasonal and prepared so that the flavours did not overwhelm the ingredients. This one of the more memorable meals I have in a long time in Vancouver.
Excellent food! Super friendly service. Delicious cocktails and a killer wine list. This is a great spot. Looking forward to many fantastic meals here.

First time and won t be the last. It didn t disappoint at all! Fresh, delicious pairings, amazing wine and service. Thank you to Avi and the team for a great first night trying your wonderful cozy restaurant.

Best new restaurant 2023 in Vancouver!  All those in the know... already know this talented team comes with a great pedigree.  Its all in the details and they are on point on all details.  The brioche with liver pate/foie gras with the concord grape compote was beyond... it may beat every Parisian version Ive ever had.  The ingredients ... such as the tomatoes...were noteworthy.  The hen of the woods was so finely dusted prior to the deep fry... it was astonishing.  Congrats and I have already booked myself in for 2 more dates as I know this city will make it difficult to get in once word spreads. Vegetarian options: Many options and delicious. Dietary restrictions: They were so helpful with suggestions.

Wow! that is the first word that me and my girlfriend said after finishing our dinner date at Garys. Where to start? they have done everything remarkably on their FIRST opening day. Ambience : We love, love the decorations and the ambience, combining simple white and black color. The space is small but feels very warm and comforting Foods : We got the 64$ menu per person for two people which allow us to get 2 snacks, two appetizers, two main course and a dessert. The foods are actually above our expectations. We know we will get good foods, but we expect to eat at duffins or panago after because we thought we will be still hungry due to the portion in reality, the foods portion is PERFECT for two people. Flavour wise, combining fresh ingredients from local farms and fisheries, we feel that every food has been given much thought, care and love. Everything is fresh, from the lettuce to the lingcod. Our favourite of the night was the pork cheek. WE DONT HAVE TO CHEW IT!! it was so tender and so much flavours. Service : top notch service. Jes served us yesterday and she was so informative, polite and very thoughtful, explaining the menu and cater to my girlfriends spice intolerance very very seriously. She feels like a friend, not a server! Also, I drink lots and lots of water, so i appreciate tht they put a bottle of water on our table! Overall 5/5. We will come back and TELL our friends to come here because we believe Garys is a great place to be and a place for people to feel comfortable, full and feel welcomed everytime. GOOD JOB!

Gary s exceeded my expectations. The vibe is unique, relaxed, peaceful and feels like the entire staff is working in unison. The food was exceptional, and our dietary restrictions were accommodated with care by Anna. Thank you for a great experience!
Absolutely fantastic! A must visit in Vancouver. Make sure to do the chefs menu and enjoy an incredible variety of food. Will definitely be coming back!
The food was absolutely delicious, the service was impeccable, and the ambiance was delightful. A perfect place for a memorable dining experience. Highly recommend!

Weve been waiting for Garys to open since it was first announced. We went last night and had a great meal! Awesome selection of wines both by the bottle and a rotating selection by the glass. The food menu was the perfect size. A good amount of choice without being overwhelming. We debated getting the menu for the table (very reasonable price!) but elected to make our own selections. Two small plates, two large plates, and two desserts was the ideal amount of food for the two of us. The service was excellent! Jess was super friendly and made some great wine recommendations to pair with the food! For the quality of food and the level of service, I think the price is very fair! Well definitely be back a lot!

Words can t describe how good this place is, you just have to try it for yourself! Gary s has it all; great food, amazing service, and a wonderful atmosphere. I can t wait to come again, and again, and again.

Youre never sure how well things will go when you show up in the first few weeks of a restaurants life, but our meal at Garys shortly after it opened was just absolutely lovely. The food was excellent (the parfait and concord grape jelly on brioche was a stand out but everything was delicious). Servers were attentive and knowledgeable, and the room is inviting and comfortable. If you opt for dessert, the chocolate mousse is a lot and probably could have been half the size for something so rich, but thats hardly something to hold against them. We are absolutely looking forward to our next visit.

What a fantastic find. Food was amazing and I loved how they presented everything, it was so much fun and relaxing all at the same time, thanks Jess!. LOVED the atmosphere and will recommend to everyone one but really we just want to keep this secret to ourselves.

Gary s is one of the greatest meals I ve had in Vancouver. I could see this restaurant getting a Michelin star one day! I recommend getting the chef tasting menu. Such a good price for all of the food you get too  . Food
Steelhead trout, beef spaetzle and chocolate mousse are our favorites. Service is impeccable. Dont think, just eat.

Very beautiful restaurant with amazing food! Service was beyond excellent and I really appreciated the care that was taken to help us with wine and to accommodate allergies. The tasting menu was one of the best I have ever done and it was very reasonably priced! Definitely recommend for anyone looking for a great experience and beautiful food!

Recently got a chance to check out Gary s with some colleagues and we weren t disappointed, beautiful little restaurant with a lovely atmosphere and even better food. We had the chefs menu for the table which was recommended which was absolutely spot on, the food was amazing, the flavours and variation of plates were incredible and for the quality and quantity of the food it was really reasonable price. Thank you to chef Matthew and Bailey and the rest of your brilliant team, couldn t recommend any higher and will be coming back.

Garys was a great dinning experience. We ordered the Tasting menue for 2. The service was so friendly, knowledgeable and provided great descriptions of the food. The dishes were not over complicated, so every ingredient was purposeful and elegant. Garys did a great job of highlighting tasty local products such as the Butter lettuce and Mussles. This was such a great experience I will be back for sure.

Enjoyed the multi course menu for the table at Gary s with some friends and was delighted by the variety, presentation and taste of the kitchens creations. The staff welcomed us warmly and created a comforting atmosphere sharing details about the dishes. The steelhead and raw beef tartare dishes really stood out along with an elderberry spirit that I ll be back for!

I was so impressed with the menu I want to go back to see and taste what the future holds. So many flavours that melded perfectly. Great new spot to dine. The service staff was knowledgeable on the menu as well.

Amazing food, service (special shout out to our server, Jess), and space. A thoughtful menu that s beautifully presented. Love the focus on locally sourced ingredients. A wonderful addition to South Granville. Highly recommend!

Great new neighborhood restaurant. Perfect for night out with friends or a cozy date night. Loved their wine selection and the food menu was very well executed comfort style French food. The foie-gras parfait on brioche toast and half Cornish hen were our favorites of the night! Super excited to come back and see how this restaurant will grow!

Incredible food in an incredibly approachable setting! Had the chefs tasting menu with pals and felt well guided, warmly looked after and DELIGHTED by the flavours. So many dishes that reached new levels from the obvious love of local produce and skills that let them shine. Can t wait to head back.
We got the tasting menu. Everything was delicious and well balanced. Cocktails were great. Ambiance and service was great. Will be coming back.
It was really fun to try everything with the chefs selection. It was DELICIOUS and I left happy and full. The staff were really knowledgeable and super attentive.
Reminds me of Montreal. Delicious, no fuss, non-pretentious dining experience. Great ingredients, straightforward food, good service. Will continue to support them as long as Im in Vancouver.
Fantastic new restaurant. Ate almost the whole menu and liked every single dish. Highly recommend!
Cream on the  , So amazing Restaurants! Great taste, environment and service. Specially chef Mathew , Bailey and Jessi ! Food
Menu is fantastic. The wine list has many gems from around the world. Lovely people making great food in a great, comfortable room. Awesome addition to the citys dining scene.
What a great addition to Vancouver restaurant scene. Delicious food, amazing service and great looking dining room.
had the tasting menu. 64pp. simple food made really well with excellent ingredients. great neighborhood place!
Everything was delicious! Service top notch. Lovely, warm, unfussy atmosphere
Excellent food, fantastic environment. Would definitely return.
Ive been waiting for something to snag this space and Garys was worth the wait. I cant wait to come back
Best restaurant in Vancouver. Thank you Gary. Dietary restrictions: Very accommodating Food : 5/5 |
new gem in Vancouver - great everything
Awesome new neighbourhood spot.
Incredible food.  Outstanding service.

So happy and excited that another fantastic restaurant has come to South Granville. Food was outstanding, especially the pork and spetzl, and pate on toast.  The blue cheese salad was also divine, as were the fabulous wines we tried. The only reason this isn t getting all 5/5 s is it was so incredibly loud it was nearly impossible to have a conversation.
